{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_kaffirlily_ver01/data/sn82007637/00340580382/1945081001/0976.xml":{"full_text":"Friday, August 10, 1945\nNow that the FAC has ac\nquired enough signatures to as\nsure us that the PR repeal refer\nendum will be on the November\nballot, we should remember we\nstill have a big job ahead.\nWe know it is the duty\nof everyone 21 years of age who\nlives in the city limits to regis\nter. Ask your friends if they\n-.are registered. If not, ask them\ndo so at once.\nOne of the strange facts that\nhave showed up in this P. R.\ndrive is that the greater part of\nToledo\u2019s naturalized citizens are\nregistered and vote in every\nelection. This proves that the\npeople who are born in this\ncountry will have to be talked\n\u2018to and shown they should be\nleading the parade. Please regis\nter at 217 Superior Street, Time:\n9.00 A. M. to 5:00 P. M.\nVote \u201cYES\u2019\u2019 on the P. R. Re\ncall and \u201cNO\u201d on changing the\nterm of councilmen from two\nyears to four years. We have\ncouncilmen now who are abso\nlutely no good for any city and\ntwo years is too long. What are\n.we going to do if they change\nCit to four years. Vote \u201cNO\u201d on\nthis change. Vote \u201cYES\u201d on\nchanging from PR to plurality\nmethod of electing councilmen.\nIMPORTANT\nWe have many back pay\nchecks dating back several years\nand a great many for those who\nworked in Departments listed\nbelow, between July 24, 1944\nand April 1, 1945. If you think\nthat you or any of your friends\nhave one coming, please mail a\npenny post card to the Willys\nUnit, 425 Winthrop Street, giv\ning name, address, badge and\nSocial Security number. We will\ncheck same for you and let you\nknow. Your officers worked\n^Champion Unit\nSparklets\nCHAMPION SPARKLETS\nPICNIC\nDon\u2019t forget the Champion\npicnic on Aug. 12. Tickets will\nbe distributed on Friday or Sat\nurday at the plant. The affair\nwill again be held at Willow\nBeach Park on lower Summit\nAve. and will begin at 11:00\na. m.\nFree rides, ice cream, pop and\nother things for the kiddies, and\nfor the big boys and girls\nstronger refreshments. Races,\nclowns, a German Band and lots\n\u25a0Jof fun are promised this year\nuntil 6:00 p. m. In the evening\na high\ndancing\ncut the\nto send\nand satisfied.\ndance band will play for danc\ning. Plan on attending. It\u2019s\ngonna be good.\nclass floor show and\nwill conspire to round\nday with a guarantee\nyou home happy, tired\nPretz Russell\u2019s\nWHEEL\nALIGNMENT\nDANGER\nIS EVIH PRJESENT\nWhen Your Wheels\nNeed Aligning\nELIMINATE\nHard Steering, Shimmy,\nExcessive Tire Wear\nGERWER\u2019S\n1415 Adams MA. 8938\nI\nhard to get this back pay for\nyou You earned\nit, so\nclaim it.\nDEPTS.\n100 102 103 104\n105 126 160 161\n16.3 164 JI 65 166\n169 170 172 175\n184 192 194 200\n201 207 208 209\n217 220 i22 223\n233 239 242 243\n244 260 261 262\n263 265 266 267\n268 270* 272 273\n300 301 306 307\n308 309 210 318\n320 321 322 323\n324 327 329 331\n334 336 339 340\n341 342 346 348\n351 354 355 356\n357 358 360 361\n362 364 365 366\n367 368 369 370\n371 381 382 383\n400 401 402 403\n404 405 420 423\n425 440 441 460\n462 463 464 480\n482 502 521 540\n541 542 545 563\n564 580 581 582\n583 584 600 602\n605 606 607 608\n610 611 620 621\n625 640 641 645\n650 661 662 665\n666 667 668 672\n680 681 685 686\n689 695 900 901\n980 98l 982 983\n984\nTune\n985 987\nIn WTOL TMtHiy Af\nAmpro\nAMPRO NEWS\nHave you noticed the picture\nof our curly-headed, chairman,\nMac Biddle in the Local 12\nyear book? Read that book,\nit'll do you good.\nMel Hannekin and John Gee\nare leaving for a new job-Jap\nexterminators. Good luck.\nVital statistics: Bill Morslock\nsired a baby boy. Rudolph Rugge\ntoo unto himself Missus Rugge,\nJuly 27.\nWhen they win, the girls soft\nball team promises to\nwith a chicken dinner,\ngal\u2019i, we love chicken.\ncoma up\nLet\u2019s go\nhis vaca\nPat Patterson is on\ntion, fishing and other things.\nWalter Fraquer took his vaca\ntion and reports that his chick\nens and garden kept him busy.\nHave you observed the goofy\nlooks, or is it lovelight in the\neyes of those newlywed Cora\nLynn and Ray Hinger?\nWe are proud of our men\u2019s\nsoftball team. Tied for first\nplace with the good Spicer team.\nIt goes to show what teamwork\ncan ccomplish.\nRalph Decker recently had his\ncar stolen.\nClyde Bryan never misses\nsoftball game. We ought to go\nand keep the guy company.\nMany gifts and cards were\nsent to our cook, Katherine Cur\nson of the cafeteria who was\nseriously burned at work last\nweek. She is in Toledo Hospi\ntal. We all -wish her a speedy\nrecovery.\nSome of the girls in the Air\nCorps inspection were burned\nout of their apartments in the\nMarlowe building fire last Sat\ndee. Our people gave them a\nhelping hand.\nWrn. Amos is exercising and\ntraining his coon dogs in the\nhope of copping some of the\nautumn prize money.\nAccording to the negotiating\ncommittee the contract now is\ngoing before concilliation. A spe\ncial meeting will be called in the\nnear future. Watch for the no\ntice on the bulletin boards.\nEiEmuraiL MANUFACTURERS\u2019\n1 ELECTRICAL SERVICE\nEDMOND LeFORT\u2014207 MAIN STREET\nTAylor 4739 Evenings TAylor 4528\n(MEMBER CIO)\nComplete Plant Electrical Mafrit finance\nEmployees\nProp. Bruce Strain\nWeServe\nToledo Stamping Ragging The\nNotes Scale\nCommutator\nT. m.\nNews\nComments\nCOMMUTATOR COMMENTS\nSteel Products\n*!O Open\na\nBy\nFavorite song \u00bbf L.w\u00abm D\u00abn theI?\u2019 .Co,u\u2018dn ,*hhat\nMy wife\u2019s Gone to the Coun- \u2018hem \u2018hcn\ntry.\u201d Of course, he\u2019ll be good lposl,\u2019\u2019 Look ln \u201c,1* wi\u201c you\n^\u00b1n\u2019he'\u2019 ,One' W\u00b0n \u00b0Note to Jake Yoav.now-\nfUTha dhaiif 7\u2122Pfnr ohviniid0n the 4th floor\u2019 everyone\nCash prizes were awarded\nPawlicki, Donald Logan, Bonnie\nSauers, Carl Olinski. Barbara\nn\nModrzynski and K. Ulinski\nwill be among the courses given\nBill Kenny\nThe grie